## Removed from Watch List (this run)
- gorilla/mux (Go): Now waymark project.
- bleach (Python): nh3 is the endorsed, actively maintained replacement (v0.3.3, Feb 2026).
- gorilla/websocket (Go): coder/websocket is maintained replacement.
- mitchellh/mapstructure (Go): go-viper/mapstructure is blessed fork (760 importers, v2 released).
- satori/go.uuid (Go): gofrs/uuid is established fork.
- ghodss/yaml (Go): sigs.k8s.io/yaml is Kubernetes-maintained fork (9,969 importers).
- lib/pq (Go): pgx is recommended by maintainers.
- sirupsen/logrus (Go): Maintenance mode, slog in Go 1.21+ is stdlib alternative.
- mholt/archiver (Go): mholt/archives is the author's own replacement.
- benbjohnson/clock (Go): jonboulle/clockwork alternative exists. Small scope.
- mysqljs/mysql (Node): mysql2 is maintained replacement (6 years stale, but mysql2 covers it).
- pycparser (Python): v3.0 released Jan 2026, actively maintained.
- pyasn1 (Python): Transferred to new maintainers, actively maintained.
- httplib2 (Python): v0.31.2 Jan 2026, actively maintained.
- feedparser (Python): Healthy, 12.9M downloads/month.
- mergo (Go): v1.0.2 released May 2025, frozen but maintained.

